                    "id": "f_s_doubled_scales_linearly",
                    "description": "Verifies the linear scaling of the grid with the f_s parameter: doubling f_s from 0.025 m to 0.05 m doubles every z_node value, since z_i = f_s * (exp(0.5*(i-0.5)) - 1) is linear in f_s. Spot-checks layers 1, 8, and 15 (top, middle, and bottom). Guards against regressions that pin the constant or break the linear coupling.",
